@page "/"

<h1>Blazor Strap</h1>
<p class="lead">Bootstrap 4 Components for Blazor Framework</p>

<h2>Blazorous</h2>
<p>
    If you want to manage your styles in code and use dynamic styles you can check out my other project: <a href="https://chanan.github.io/Blazorous/">Blazorous</a>.
    In the future I will show examples of mixing and matching BlazorStrap and Blazorous.
</p>

<h2>Install</h2>

<ol>
    <li>Get it from nuget: <a href="https://www.nuget.org/packages/BlazorStrap/"><img src="https://img.shields.io/nuget/vpre/BlazorStrap.svg" /></a></li>
    <li>Add <mark>@@using BlazorStrap</mark> to your <mark>_Imports.razor</mark></li>
</ol>

<h3>Server Side Usage</h3>

<p>In addition to the above, modify your <mark>_Host.cshtml</mark> file to include the javascript files used by BlazorStrap. An example of this is in the ServerSideSample project in the src folder.</p>

